meta {
  name: 4. Validate Customer - Trade
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/admin/api/v1/feedback/trade/validate-customer
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "mobile": "7607777750",
    "customerCode": "860101Z009",
    "surveyId": "SURVEY-2026-0001",
    "feedbackChannel": "SMS"
  }
}

script:post-response {
  var json = res.getBody();
  if (json.data && json.data.feedbackToken) {
      bru.setVar('feedback_token', json.data.feedbackToken);
      console.log('feedback_token saved:', json.data.feedbackToken);
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: false
  timeout: 0
}

docs {
  Step 2 of the TRADE flow (after Validate Link).
  Verifies the mobile belongs to the customer, re-checks dedup, then issues a
  feedback token. Token carries surveyId + channel (anti-tamper).

  Input:
    - mobile: 10-digit customer mobile            (REQUIRED)
    - surveyId: from the link                     (REQUIRED)
    - feedbackChannel: SMS | Email | UCC          (REQUIRED)
    - customerCode: from the link                 (OPTIONAL for TRADE)
        When present: backend loads MH_CUSTOMER by code + verifies mobile.
        When absent:  fallback resolves by mobile → PAN → LOB-priority
                      (CEMENT > BPD > UBS) and derives the customerCode.

  Outcomes:
    200 → { feedbackToken, customerName, customerCode, remainingSubmissions }
          customerCode in the response is the one stored (derived if fallback).
    404 CUSTOMER_NOT_FOUND         → customerCode doesn't exist in MH_CUSTOMER
                                      OR (in fallback) no MH_CUSTOMER row for the mobile
    400 INVALID_MOBILE_FOR_CUSTOMER → customerCode is valid but mobile doesn't match
                                      that customer
    409 FEEDBACK_ALREADY_SUBMITTED  → already filled for this survey
    400 INVALID_FEEDBACK_CHANNEL
    429 FEEDBACK_LIMIT_EXCEEDED    → 5/day hit

  Saves feedback_token into the collection var for Submit.

  NOTE: KEY / NON_TRADE segments require customerCode — no fallback available.
}
